## Explanation:

### Solution 01

- Basic approach, taking all possible cases that can happen and making a while loop for every case.
- We’ll calculate from a large value and will continue until it’s reduced to any other cases.
- Add the character to the last of the ans string.
- **Time complexity:** O(n^2).

### Solution 02

- Here we store the values of all cases in a string and int variable.
- Here 13 possible cases can happen, so we run a loop for 13 indexes.
- Similar to the previous approach runs a while loop until num is greater or equal to current number of our array & add this to our ans array.
- **Time complexity:** O(n^2).

---

